xml.fileAssociations.description:
Allows XML schemas to be associated to file name patterns.

Example:
[{
  "systemId": "path/to/file.xsd",
  "pattern": "file1.xml"
},
{
  "systemId": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema.xsdd",
  "pattern": "**/*.xsd"
}]

xml.fileAssociations.markdownDescription:
Allows XML schemas to be associated to file name patterns.

Example:
```json
[{
  "systemId": "path/to/file.xsd",
  "pattern": "file1.xml"
},
{
  "systemId": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema.xsd",
  "pattern": "**/*.xsd"
}]
```
